I"õ=<h1 id="2019-pass-the-salt-schedule">2019 Pass the SALT SCHEDULE</h1>

<hr />

<p><strong>All the slides are there:</strong> <a href="https://2019.pass-the-salt.org/files/slides/">https://2019.pass-the-salt.org/files/slides/</a></p>

<p><strong>And all the videos are also published:</strong> <a href="https://passthesalt.ubicast.tv/channels/#2019-lille">https://passthesalt.ubicast.tv/channels/#2019-lille</a></p>

<p>For this second edition, we are happy to propose to you <strong>26 talks</strong> about Security and Free Software (or open format/protocol).</p>

<p>We also want you to have the opportunity to <strong>learn and practice through 9 workshops</strong> (see their <a href="#workshops">schedule</a> below).</p>

<p>Enjoy!</p>

<div style="border-left: 5px solid #7b4397; padding-left: 10px"> <h2>Talks Schedule</h2></div>

<p>The talks schedule is designed around  <strong>7 sessions</strong> covering a wide spectrum of topics from hacking low level/crypto to security of the devops workflow or offensive research on Free Software projects, among others.</p>

